# Tailwind CSS Conventions

## CDN Configuration

Extend Tailwind config in `<head>` for custom fonts and colors:

```html
<script>
    tailwind.config = {
        theme: {
            extend: {
                fontFamily: {
                    'comic': ['"Comic Sans MS"', 'cursive'],
                    'times': ['"Times New Roman"', 'serif'],
                    'courier': ['"Courier New"', 'monospace'],
                },
                animation: {
                    'blink': 'blink 1s step-end infinite',
                    'marquee': 'marquee 15s linear infinite',
                },
                keyframes: {
                    blink: {
                        '50%': { opacity: '0' },
                    },
                    marquee: {
                        '0%': { transform: 'translateX(100%)' },
                        '100%': { transform: 'translateX(-100%)' },
                    },
                }
            }
        }
    }
</script>
```

## Common Retro Patterns

```html
<!-- Centered container with retro border -->
<div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto p-4 border-4 border-double border-cyan-400 bg-black/80">

<!-- Glowing text effect -->
<h1 class="text-pink-500 drop-shadow-[0_0_10px_rgba(236,72,153,0.8)]">

<!-- Marquee-style scroll -->
<div class="overflow-hidden whitespace-nowrap">
    <span class="inline-block animate-marquee">Welcome to my page!</span>
</div>

<!-- Blinking text (use sparingly!) -->
<span class="animate-blink text-red-500">NEW!</span>
```

## Utility Preferences

- Prefer Tailwind utilities over custom CSS
- Use arbitrary values when needed: `text-[#ff00ff]`, `w-[200px]`
- Combine utilities for complex effects via `class="..."`

## Inline Styles

Only use inline `style=""` for:
- One-off backgrounds: `style="background-image: url(...)"`
- Complex gradients not in Tailwind
